Dysfunction markets: The most valuable queries are ones where a user wants to spend a lot of money on something, but it's hard for them to know what is the right product (e.g. insurance, lawyers, emergency plumbers).

But what if chatbots make it easy to evaluate products?

Information Habits: Google makes most of it's money from a tiny fraction of queries (e.g. "car insurance"). The reason it makes the others good is so you form a habit of using search to look up anything online.

But what if chatbots start a new habit?

7. Disadvantages

- View cannot be created on temporary tables

- It cannot have parameters

- Cannot update records in view if the underlying query contains aggregate functions, Distinct, group by, union, etc

- Depending on the DB vendor it can have many more limitations

6. Advantages

- Easily hide the complexity of the query and the user can directly interact with a view like a table

- Hide raw data and show aggregated data

- Apply row/column level security

- And, also see the records in View as a normal table via a Select query
